Rating: 3
Added 2 cloves garlic, 1/2 tsp dijon, finished with ground sumac. Added 2.5 more cucumbers becuase the soup was too thin. Skipped the sour cream. Soup definately gets better with age; garlic became spicier the longer it sat. Excellent cool beginning to a meal. Great use for garden cucs. I didn't peel or seed the cucs because I used fresh garden cucs without tough waxy skin. The skin added a beautiful green hue to the soup.

