I made it as a first course for a dinner party on a very hot and humid night. I got rave reviews. I used Tzatziki instead of plain yogurt and I think it kicked up the flavour quite a bit. I used shrimp cocktail bowls with crushed ice on the bottom, toped each bowl with thinly sliced chilled cumber and slivers of red pepper for colour.

Rating: 4
Made this soup as a first course for a dinner party last weekend and it was a huge hit. Just a few alterations: use Greek-style yogurt which has a bit more flavor. Also added a pinch of cayenne pepper at the end which gave the flavor a boost. Served in chilled bowls with a seared scallop in the middle. Paired with a dry riesling. Received rave reviews from everyone. Definitely a keeper and a perfect summer soup!

